The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Business Briefs
                                                                              Thursday , November 19 , 2009                                                                                                                                                                                              Business Briefs
                              
	 Mumbai, Nov. 18: Credit offtake for the fortnight ended November 6 saw an increase of around 9 per cent, the slowest growth in 12 years. Analysts said the slowdown in credit expansion would make it difficult for the RBI to hike interest rates. According to data released by the RBI today, credit growth was up 9.07 per cent at Rs 28,73,062 crore against Rs 26,12,401 crore in the corresponding fortnight a year ago.                             
	 New Delhi, Nov. 18: The Union Bank of India aims to raise $500 million through bonds over the next four months. The bank will issue the bonds under its medium-term note programme by March 2010 to fund its overseas operations, Union Bank chairman M.V. Nair said.                            
	 New Delhi, Nov. 18: Hyundai Motor India is committed to launching a car smaller than Santro. The company plans to focus more on domestic sales.                             
	 New Delhi, Nov. 18: An empowered group of ministers will meet tomorrow to review the progress on auction of 3G mobile licences, amid a tiff between the telecom and defence ministries over release of spectrum for commercial use.                             
	 Calcutta, Nov. 18: SRMB Srijan has come up with specially designed TMT rods that can withstand earthquake.                                                                                                                           
